      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0668P0-04485'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0668P0_20050125_GCR_215' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: Subsection (6) prohibits joint investigation, joint reporting and publishing with the Scottish Public Service Ombudsman. The simple question is: why, when such joint activity is possible with all the other ombudsmen listed in subsection (7)? I beg to move
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0668P0-04486'>
        <a name='S5LV0668P0_20050125_GCR_216'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-gwilym-prys-davies' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
